[quote=“jme_009, post:6, topic:109015”]On my dvd drive, I was pressing the button and it just wouldn’t open. It would just try to run the cd that was in there. I dunno, computers are weird sometimes.[/quote]

item.title: My dvd drive is stuck
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

On my dvd drive, I was pressing the button and it just wouldn’t open. It would just try to run the cd that was in there. I went to My Computer > And I right clicked my E drive(because thats my dvd drive…) and selected eject. From then on my drive worked just fine.

I dunno, computers are weird sometimes.

Read full topic

item.title: My dvd drive is stuck
item.dc:creator: @sparkz sparkz
item.description:
@sparkz wrote:

If the tray is stuck (i.e. wont open), there should be a tiny hole underneath the tray were you can push a paper-clip into, which should release the tray. (note that it may break the DVD/CD inside the drive)
